727819f-a.text:
Queens Boulevard, south from 70th Road. The Boulevard Bank occupies a small triangular block bounded by the Boulevard, 70th Road, and 108th Street.
P. L. Sperr  May 30, 1939

727818f-a.text:
Queens Boulevard (trolley lines thereon), west from 70th Road (extreme left), showing in the background a remodeled house occupied at one time by Chas. Reitenback,a blacksmith; Van Wicklen was the owner in 1891.

August 1924.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
